3. Responsible for the testing of suspension system components, tracking of vehicle road tests, problem analysis, and rectification;

4. Responsible for the production and manufacturing of suspension system components, as well as providing technical support for after-market issues;

5. Responsible for conducting research on suspension system components and conducting benchmark analysis with competitors, introducing excellent designs from the industry, and introducing and applying new materials, processes, and technologies;

